      • FrameDetector

        public FrameDetector(android.content.Context context,
             int maxNumFaces,
             Detector.FaceDetectorMode faceDetectorMode)
        Creates a FrameProcessor.
        Parameters:
        context - application's context.
        maxNumFaces - The maximum number of faces that the system should try to track. This may slow down the system.
        faceDetectorMode - A flag to specify if the system is tracking large (up close) or small (farther away) faces. Possible values are Detector.FaceDetectorMode.LARGE_FACES or Detector.FaceDetectorMode.SMALL_FACES.

      • FrameDetector

        public FrameDetector(android.content.Context context)

        context - application's context.

      • process

        public void process(Frame frame,
           float timestamp)
        Asks the Detector to process the passed facePicture. This method is used with the constructor that does not specify a file or camera type. Callers may pass frames to this method at any rate that is suitable for them. The detector expects subsequent frames to be related to previous frames (e.g. a video stream).

        Parameters:
        frame - A Frame to process. Must be right side up: use Frame.rotateImage(android.graphics.Bitmap, float) before calling.
        timestamp - A timestamp (non-negative), in seconds; expected to be larger than the previous call to this method.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if frame is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if timestampSec is negative or is smaller than or equal to the previous call.
